{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0116YA4rYY4LKmQQwBSbMtgQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a concise report of everything requested.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\n**Helper functions (all at module top-level):**\n\n- **Line 58:** `def _find_repo_root(start: Path) -> Path`\n  Walks up from `start` until a `.git` dir is found; raises `SystemExit` if none.\n\n- **Line 68:** `def _default_prd_dir() -> Path`\n  Calls `_find_repo_root(Path.cwd())` and returns `repo / \"prds\"`.\n\n- **Line 80:** `def _default_workflows_dir() -> Path`\n  Calls `_find_repo_root(Path.cwd())` and returns `repo / \"workflows\"`.\n\n- **Line 90:** `def _load_workflows_or_fail(workflows_dir: Path) -> dict[str, Workflow]`\n  Thin wrapper — raises `SystemExit` if the dir doesn't exist, else delegates to `load_workflows`.\n\n**CLI setup (argparse, not click/typer):**\n\n- **Line 1499:** `def build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser`\n  Creates `argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"prd\")`. Global flags: `--prd-dir`, `--workflows-dir`, `--json`, `-v/--verbose`, `--theme`, `--no-color`, `--icon-set`. Registers subparsers (line 1538): `new`, `status`, `cleanup`, `next`, `validate`, `tree`, `children`, `orphans`, `undecomposed`, `conflicts`, `list-workflows`, `assign`, `normalize`, `plan`, `run`, `reconcile`.\n\n- **Line 1765:** `def main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int`\n  Entry point. Calls `build_parser()`, resolves `prd_dir` and `workflows_dir` defaults, builds a `Styler` from `resolve_style_config`, then dispatches via `args.func(args)`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `src/darkfactory/loader.py`\n\n- **Line 32:** `def load_workflows(workflows_dir: Path) -> dict[str, Workflow]`\n  Public API. Scans `workflows_dir` for subdirectories containing `workflow.py`. Skips dirs starting with `_` or `.`. Raises `ValueError` on duplicate workflow names. Import errors are logged at WARNING and skipped. Returns `{}` if the dir doesn't exist.\n\n- **Line 89:** `def _load_workflow_module(workflow_file: Path, subdir: Path) -> Workflow`\n  Private. Imports a single `workflow.py` via `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location` with a synthetic module name `_darkfactory_workflow_<dirname>` to avoid `sys.modules` collisions. Validates the module has a `workflow` attribute that is a `Workflow` instance and sets `wf.workflow_dir = subdir`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `workflows/` directory structure (top-level)\n\n```\nworkflows/\n  __init__.py\n  default/\n    __init__.py\n    workflow.py\n  extraction/\n    __init__.py\n    workflow.py\n  planning/\n    workflow.py\n```\n\nThree workflows: `default`, `extraction`, `planning`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `pyproject.toml` scripts section\n\n`/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/pyproject.toml`, `[project.scripts]`:\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\nprd = \"darkfactory.cli:main\"\n```\n\nSingle entry point: the `prd` command invokes `darkfactory.cli.main`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Config loading code\n\nConfig is in `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/src/darkfactory/style.py`.\n\n- **Line 380:** `def resolve_style_config(*, theme: str | None = None, icon_set: str | None = None, no_color: bool = False, repo_root: Path | None = None) -> StyleConfig`\n\nPrecedence (highest wins):\n1. CLI flags (`--theme`, `--icon-set`, `--no-color`)\n2. Env vars: `DARKFACTORY_THEME`, `DARKFACTORY_ICON_SET`, `NO_COLOR`\n3. Project config: `<repo_root>/.darkfactory/config.toml`\n4. User config: `~/.config/darkfactory/config.toml`\n5. Built-in defaults (dark theme, ascii icons, color on)\n\nThis is style-only config — there is no separate general-purpose application config loader. The `style.py` helper `_merge_toml_file` is the only config-file-reading code in the codebase."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"939fc375-8ed1-4dc0-8515-8b3ee2d79451","uuid":"4d9db154-7183-4607-97eb-4339ae1fde37","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:38:25.674Z",