`start` looking for a `.darkfactory/` directory.\n2. Add a `resolve_project_root(cli_dir: Path | None, env_var: str | None, cwd: Path) -> Path` function that applies the resolution order: CLI flag > env var > walk-up discovery from cwd.\n3. If no `.darkfactory/` is found in any parent, the function returns `None`. The CLI should print a clear error: \"No `.darkfactory/` directory found. Run `prd init` to set up this project.\" and exit 1.\n4. Add `--directory` / `-C` as a global argument in `build_parser()` (line ~1499 in `cli.py`).\n5. Read `DARKFACTORY_DIR` env var as fallback when `--directory` is not provided.\n6. Replace `_find_repo_root`, `_default_prd_dir`, and `_default_workflows_dir` in `cli.py` with calls to the new discovery module. The `prd_dir` becomes `<discovered>/.darkfactory/prds/` and workflows dir becomes `<discovered>/.darkfactory/workflows/`.\n7. No special-case detection for \"am I in darkfactory's own repo\" — the tool always looks for `.darkfactory/`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/discovery.py`\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport os\n\ndef find_darkfactory_dir(start: Path) -> Path | None:\n    \"\"\"Walk up from start looking for a .darkfactory/ directory.\"\"\"\n    current = start.resolve()\n    while True:\n        candidate = current / \".darkfactory\"\n        if candidate.is_dir():\n            return candidate\n        parent = current.parent\n        if parent == current:\n            return None\n        current = parent\n\ndef resolve_project_root(\n    cli_dir: Path | None = None,\n    cwd: Path | None = None,\n) -> Path | None:\n    \"\"\"Resolve the .darkfactory directory.\n\n    Priority: --directory CLI flag > DARKFACTORY_DIR env > walk-up from cwd.\n    \"\"\"\n    if cli_dir is not None:\n        df = cli_dir / \".darkfactory\"\n        return df if df.is_dir() else None\n\n    env_dir = os.environ.get(\"DARKFACTORY_DIR\")\n    if env_dir:\n        df = Path(env_dir) / \".darkfactory\"\n        return df if df.is_dir() else None\n\n    return find_darkfactory_dir(cwd or Path.cwd())\n```\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\n- Remove `_find_repo_root` (line 58), `_default_prd_dir` (line 68), `_default_workflows_dir` (line 80).\n- In `build_parser()`, add `--directory` / `-C` as a top-level argument before subparsers.\n- In `main()`, call `resolve_project_root(args.directory)` and derive `prd_dir` and `workflows_dir` from the result.\n- Subcommands that currently accept `--prd-dir` / `--workflows-dir` keep working as explicit overrides; the discovery path is only the default.\n\n### `tests/test_discovery.py`\n\n- Test walk-up finds `.darkfactory/` in parent directories.\n- Test `--directory` override takes precedence.\n- Test `DARKFACTORY_DIR` env var takes precedence over walk-up.\n- Test CLI flag beats env var.\n- Test returns `None` when no `.darkfactory/` exists anywhere.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `find_darkfactory_dir()` correctly walks up and finds `.darkfactory/` in ancestor directories.\n- [ ] AC-2: `--directory /some/path` causes the CLI to use `/some/path/.darkfactory/` as the project root.\n- [ ] AC-3: `DARKFACTORY_DIR=/some/path` env var works when `--directory` is not provided.\n- [ ] AC-4: CLI flag wins over env var.\n- [ ] AC-5: When no `.darkfactory/` is found, `prd status` (and other subcommands) prints a clear error mentioning `prd init` and exits 1.\n- [ ] AC-6: No dev-mode fallback or special-case detection for darkfactory's own repo.\n- [ ] AC-7: Existing `--prd-dir` and `--workflows-dir` flags still work as explicit overrides.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0192hxgRq4xUhSdhBVoZK3w7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RGnETiRfze13m3eaBPodjB","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/prds/PRD-222.2-prd-init-subcommand.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-222.2\"\ntitle: \"prd init subcommand\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-222-general-purpose-tool]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.1-config-directory-discovery]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.8-dogfood-move-state]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/cli.py\n  - src/darkfactory/init.py\n  - tests/test_init.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - cli\n---\n\n# prd init subcommand\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd a `prd init` subcommand that scaffolds the `.darkfactory/` directory structure in the current (or `--directory`-specified) project. This creates the standard directory layout, writes a starter `config.toml` with commented examples, and updates `.gitignore` to exclude runtime state directories. The command is idempotent — re-running on an already-initialized project reports \"already initialized\" and makes no changes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. `prd init` creates the following structure at the target project root:\n   - `.darkfactory/prds/` (empty)\n   - `.darkfactory/workflows/` (empty)\n   - `.darkfactory/config.toml` (skeleton with commented examples)\n   - `.darkfactory/worktrees/` (empty, will be git-ignored)\n   - `.darkfactory/transcripts/` (empty, will be git-ignored)\n2. Updates (or creates) `.gitignore` at the project root to include:\n   - `.darkfactory/worktrees/`\n   - `.darkfactory/transcripts/`\n3. The command requires a `.git/` directory in the target — if absent, error with \"Not a git repository. Run `git init` first.\"\n4. Idempotent: if `.darkfactory/` already exists with the expected structure, print \"Already initialized\" and exit 0 without modifying anything.\n5. If `.darkfactory/` partially exists (e.g. `prds/` exists but `workflows/` does not), fill in the missing pieces without overwriting existing files.\n6. The `config.toml` skeleton should contain commented-out examples for common settings (model defaults, timeout overrides) so users can see what's available.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/init.py`\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nGITIGNORE_ENTRIES = [\n    \".darkfactory/worktrees/\",\n    \".darkfactory/transcripts/\",\n]\n\nCONFIG_SKELETON = \"\"\"\\\n# Darkfactory project configuration\n# See https://darkfactory.dev/docs/config for all options\n\n# [model]\n# trivial = \"haiku\"\n# simple = \"sonnet\"\n# moderate = \"sonnet\"\n# complex = \"opus\"\n\n# [timeouts]\n# xs = 5    # minutes\n# s = 10\n# m = 20\n# l = 40\n# xl = 75\n\"\"\"\n\ndef init_project(target: Path) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Scaffold .darkfactory/ in target. Returns status message.\"\"\"\n    ...\n```\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\n- Register `init` subparser in `build_parser()` alongside existing subcommands.\n- The `init` handler does NOT require `.darkfactory/` to already exist (bypass discovery for this one subcommand).\n- Wire `args.func` to call `init_project(target)`.\n\n### `tests/test_init.py`\n\n- Test scaffolding in a fresh git repo (tmp_path with `git init`).\n- Test idempotency — run twice, second run reports \"Already initialized\".\n- Test partial fill-in — remove one subdir, re-run, only missing piece is created.\n- Test `.gitignore` creation and update (append without duplicating entries).\n- Test error when no `.git/` directory exists.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `prd init` in a fresh git repo creates the full `.darkfactory/` structure.\n- [ ] AC-2: `.gitignore` is updated with runtime-state exclusions.\n- [ ] AC-3: Re-running `prd init` reports \"Already initialized\" and makes no changes.\n- [ ] AC-4: Partial `.darkfactory/` is completed without overwriting existing files.\n- [ ] AC-5: `config.toml` contains commented examples of available settings.\n- [ ] AC-6: Running in a directory without `.git/` produces a clear error.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1859,"cache_read_input_tokens":29551,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1859},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"939fc375-8ed1-4dc0-8515-8b3ee2d79451","uuid":"62c85e67-fdf2-4813-b740-fbc2bd9c3b6d"}
