directory once the loader is switched over.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Move `workflows/default/` to `src/darkfactory/workflows/default/`.\n2. Move `workflows/extraction/` to `src/darkfactory/workflows/extraction/`.\n3. Move `workflows/planning/` to `src/darkfactory/workflows/planning/`.\n4. Create or update `src/darkfactory/workflows/__init__.py` to expose a function `get_builtin_workflows() -> dict[str, Workflow]` that imports and returns all three built-in workflows.\n5. Update `loader.py`'s `load_workflows()` to accept a source specifier or add a new `load_builtin_workflows()` function that discovers workflows from the package rather than a filesystem directory.\n6. Delete the old top-level `workflows/` directory (and its `__init__.py`).\n7. All existing tests that reference workflows continue to pass after the move.\n8. Built-in workflow modules must be importable as `darkfactory.workflows.default`, `darkfactory.workflows.extraction`, `darkfactory.workflows.planning`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### Moving workflow files\n\n```\nworkflows/default/    → src/darkfactory/workflows/default/\nworkflows/extraction/ → src/darkfactory/workflows/extraction/\nworkflows/planning/   → src/darkfactory/workflows/planning/\n```\n\nEach subdirectory keeps its `__init__.py` and `workflow.py`. The top-level `workflows/__init__.py` is replaced by `src/darkfactory/workflows/__init__.py`.\n\n### `src/darkfactory/workflows/__init__.py`\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom darkfactory.loader import _load_workflow_module\nfrom darkfactory.models import Workflow\n\nBUILTIN_WORKFLOW_NAMES = [\"default\", \"extraction\", \"planning\"]\n\ndef get_builtin_workflows() -> dict[str, Workflow]:\n    \"\"\"Load all built-in workflows shipped with the package.\"\"\"\n    result = {}\n    base = Path(__file__).parent\n    for name in BUILTIN_WORKFLOW_NAMES:\n        subdir = base / name\n        wf_file = subdir / \"workflow.py\"\n        if wf_file.exists():\n            wf = _load_workflow_module(wf_file, subdir)\n            result[name] = wf\n    return result\n```\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/loader.py`\n\n- Extract `_load_workflow_module` as a semi-public helper (rename to `load_workflow_module` or keep private but importable within the package).\n- `load_workflows(workflows_dir)` continues to work for filesystem-based workflow loading (used by user-level and project-level layers).\n- Add or expose `load_builtin_workflows()` that delegates to `get_builtin_workflows()`.\n\n### Cleanup\n\n- Delete `workflows/` at the repo top level after confirming all references point to the new location.\n- Update any test fixtures or conftest that reference the old `workflows/` path.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `default`, `extraction`, and `planning` workflows exist under `src/darkfactory/workflows/` and are importable as Python modules.\n- [ ] AC-2: `get_builtin_workflows()` returns all three built-in workflows.\n- [ ] AC-3: The old top-level `workflows/` directory is deleted.\n- [ ] AC-4: Existing tests pass after the move.\n- [ ] AC-5: A `pip install -e .` or `uv tool install` includes the workflow files in the installed package.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0192hxgRq4xUhSdhBVoZK3w7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BMcsTTd85Dhtu7E3sQW2oS","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/prds/PRD-222.4-user-config-directory.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-222.4\"\ntitle: \"User config directory (~/.config/darkfactory/)\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-222-general-purpose-tool]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.5-cascade-resolver-workflows]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-222.6-cascade-resolver-config]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/paths.py\n  - tests/test_paths.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - config\n---\n\n# User config directory (~/.config/darkfactory/)\n\n## Summary\n\nCreate a `paths.py` module that resolves the user-level config directory (`~/.config/darkfactory/`) honoring `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`. This module provides the canonical path functions used by the cascade resolvers (PRD-222.5, PRD-222.6) to discover user-level workflows and config. The workflows subdirectory is created on first access if missing; `config.toml` is lazy (absent means no user overrides).\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/paths.py` with functions to resolve user-level paths:\n   - `user_config_dir() -> Path` — returns `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/darkfactory/` or `~/.config/darkfactory/`.\n   - `user_config_file() -> Path | None` — returns the path to `config.toml` if it exists, else `None`.\n   - `user_workflows_dir() -> Path` — returns the workflows subdirectory, creating it if absent.\n2. Honor `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME` if set; otherwise default to `~/.config/`.\n3. The `workflows/` subdirectory is created on first access (so users can drop files in without manually creating the dir).\n4. `config.toml` is never auto-created — its absence simply means \"no user-level overrides.\"\n5. Platform-appropriate: on macOS use `~/.config/` (XDG is common there too), not `~/Library/`. Keep it simple and consistent with the XDG convention.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/paths.py`\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport os\n\ndef user_config_dir() -> Path:\n    \"\"\"Return the user-level darkfactory config directory.\"\"\"\n    xdg = os.environ.get(\"XDG_CONFIG_HOME\")\n    base = Path(xdg) if xdg else Path.home() / \".config\"\n    return base / \"darkfactory\"\n\ndef user_config_file() -> Path | None:\n    \"\"\"Return path to user config.toml if it exists.\"\"\"\n    f = user_config_dir() / \"config.toml\"\n    return f if f.is_file() else None\n\ndef user_workflows_dir() -> Path:\n    \"\"\"Return user workflows dir, creating if absent.\"\"\"\n    d = user_config_dir() / \"workflows\"\n    d.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    return d\n```\n\n### `tests/test_paths.py`\n\n- Test `user_config_dir()` returns `~/.config/darkfactory/` by default.\n- Test `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` override.\n- Test `user_config_file()` returns `None` when file doesn't exist.\n- Test `user_workflows_dir()` creates the directory.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `user_config_dir()` returns `~/.config/darkfactory/` when `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` is unset.\n- [ ] AC-2: `user_config_dir()` respects `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME` when set.\n- [ ] AC-3: `user_workflows_dir()` creates the directory if it doesn't exist.\n- [ ] AC-4: `user_config_file()` returns `None` when no `config.toml` exists.\n- [ ] AC-5: All path functions are pure (no side effects except the mkdir in `user_workflows_dir`).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1859,"cache_read_input_tokens":29551,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1859},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"939fc375-8ed1-4dc0-8515-8b3ee2d79451","uuid":"22a770bc-8db4-4f04-8238-9a49bd5caa14"}
