dir() -> Path` — returns the workflows subdirectory, creating it if absent.\n2. Honor `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME` if set; otherwise default to `~/.config/`.\n3. The `workflows/` subdirectory is created on first access (so users can drop files in without manually creating the dir).\n4. `config.toml` is never auto-created — its absence simply means \"no user-level overrides.\"\n5. Platform-appropriate: on macOS use `~/.config/` (XDG is common there too), not `~/Library/`. Keep it simple and consistent with the XDG convention.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/paths.py`\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport os\n\ndef user_config_dir() -> Path:\n    \"\"\"Return the user-level darkfactory config directory.\"\"\"\n    xdg = os.environ.get(\"XDG_CONFIG_HOME\")\n    base = Path(xdg) if xdg else Path.home() / \".config\"\n    return base / \"darkfactory\"\n\ndef user_config_file() -> Path | None:\n    \"\"\"Return path to user config.toml if it exists.\"\"\"\n    f = user_config_dir() / \"config.toml\"\n    return f if f.is_file() else None\n\ndef user_workflows_dir() -> Path:\n    \"\"\"Return user workflows dir, creating if absent.\"\"\"\n    d = user_config_dir() / \"workflows\"\n    d.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    return d\n```\n\n### `tests/test_paths.py`\n\n- Test `user_config_dir()` returns `~/.config/darkfactory/` by default.\n- Test `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` override.\n- Test `user_config_file()` returns `None` when file doesn't exist.\n- Test `user_workflows_dir()` creates the directory.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `user_config_dir()` returns `~/.config/darkfactory/` when `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` is unset.\n- [ ] AC-2: `user_config_dir()` respects `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME` when set.\n- [ ] AC-3: `user_workflows_dir()` creates the directory if it doesn't exist.\n- [ ] AC-4: `user_config_file()` returns `None` when no `config.toml` exists.\n- [ ] AC-5: All path functions are pure (no side effects except the mkdir in `user_workflows_dir`).\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0192hxgRq4xUhSdhBVoZK3w7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013RAKc8zrtpL1u6DDif5cva","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/prds/PRD-222.5-cascade-resolver-workflows.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-222.5\"\ntitle: \"Cascade resolver for workflows\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: m\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-222-general-purpose-tool]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.1-config-directory-discovery]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-222.3-bundle-builtin-workflows]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-222.4-user-config-directory]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.8-dogfood-move-state]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/loader.py\n  - src/darkfactory/registry.py\n  - tests/test_registry.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - config\n---\n\n# Cascade resolver for workflows\n\n## Summary\n\nBuild a unified workflow registry that discovers workflows from all three layers (built-in, user, project), validates each against the workflow API contract, and enforces strict name uniqueness across layers. Any name collision is a hard error at startup. Any workflow failing API validation is a hard error with a clear diagnostic message naming the layer, file path, and specific violation.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/registry.py` with a `build_workflow_registry(project_dir: Path | None) -> dict[str, Workflow]` function.\n2. The registry collects workflows from three layers in order:\n   - **Built-in**: from `darkfactory.workflows.get_builtin_workflows()` (PRD-222.3).\n   - **User**: from `~/.config/darkfactory/workflows/` via `load_workflows()` (PRD-222.4 paths).\n   - **Project**: from `<project>/.darkfactory/workflows/` via `load_workflows()` (PRD-222.1 discovery).\n3. **Collision detection**: if any workflow name appears in more than one layer, raise `WorkflowNameCollision` with a message naming all conflicting paths. This is fatal — no subcommand runs.\n4. **API validation**: every discovered workflow is validated at load time against the expected contract (must be a `Workflow` instance with required attributes: `name`, `steps`, `applies_to`). Failures raise `InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, reason)`. Fatal.\n5. Both error types print actionable remediation hints:\n   - Collision: \"Workflow 'X' found in multiple layers: [paths]. Rename or delete one to resolve.\"\n   - Invalid: \"Workflow at [path] (layer: [layer]) failed validation: [reason].\"\n6. Replace the current `_load_workflows_or_fail` in `cli.py` with a call to `build_workflow_registry()`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/registry.py`\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom darkfactory.models import Workflow\nfrom darkfactory.loader import load_workflows\nfrom darkfactory.workflows import get_builtin_workflows\nfrom darkfactory.paths import user_workflows_dir\n\nclass WorkflowNameCollision(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised when the same workflow name appears in multiple layers.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\nclass InvalidWorkflow(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a workflow fails API contract validation.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\ndef _validate_workflow(wf: Workflow, layer: str, path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Validate a workflow against the expected API contract.\"\"\"\n    if not hasattr(wf, 'name') or not wf.name:\n        raise InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, \"'name' attribute is missing or empty\")\n    if not hasattr(wf, 'steps') or not isinstance(wf.steps, list):\n        raise InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, f\"'steps' must be a list; got {type(wf.steps).__name__}\")\n    if not hasattr(wf, 'applies_to') or not callable(wf.applies_to):\n        raise InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, \"'applies_to' must be callable\")\n\ndef build_workflow_registry(project_dir: Path | None = None) -> dict[str, Workflow]:\n    \"\"\"Discover, validate, and return all workflows from all layers.\"\"\"\n    registry: dict[str, tuple[str, Path, Workflow]] = {}\n\n    # Layer 1: built-in\n    for name, wf in get_builtin_workflows().items():\n        _validate_workflow(wf, \"built-in\", Path(\"<package>\") / name)\n        registry[name] = (\"built-in\", Path(\"<package>\") / name, wf)\n\n    # Layer 2: user\n    user_dir = user_workflows_dir()\n    if user_dir.is_dir():\n        for name, wf in load_workflows(user_dir).items():\n            _validate_workflow(wf, \"user\", user_dir / name)\n            if name in registry:\n                existing_layer, existing_path, _ = registry[name]\n                raise WorkflowNameCollision(name, [\n                    (existing_layer, existing_path),\n                    (\"user\", user_dir / name),\n                ])\n            registry[name] = (\"user\", user_dir / name, wf)\n\n    # Layer 3: project\n    if project_dir:\n        proj_wf_dir = project_dir / \"workflows\"\n        if proj_wf_dir.is_dir():\n            for name, wf in load_workflows(proj_wf_dir).items():\n                _validate_workflow(wf, \"project\", proj_wf_dir / name)\n                if name in registry:\n                    existing_layer, existing_path, _ = registry[name]\n                    raise WorkflowNameCollision(name, [\n                        (existing_layer, existing_path),\n                        (\"project\", proj_wf_dir / name),\n                    ])\n                registry[name] = (\"project\", proj_wf_dir / name, wf)\n\n    return {name: wf for name, (_, _, wf) in registry.items()}\n```\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\n- Replace `_load_workflows_or_fail()` (line 90) with a call to `build_workflow_registry(darkfactory_dir)`.\n- Error handling: catch `WorkflowNameCollision` and `InvalidWorkflow` in `main()`, print the message, and exit 1.\n\n### `tests/test_registry.py`\n\nTable-driven tests covering:\n- Built-in only (no user/project dirs).\n- User-only workflows discovered correctly.\n- Project-only workflows discovered correctly.\n- Built-in + project with no collision — all merged.\n- Collision between built-in and user.\n- Collision between built-in and project.\n- Collision between user and project.\n- Invalid workflow in each layer (missing name, bad steps type, non-callable applies_to).\n- Each error message includes layer, path, and specific violation.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: Workflows from all three layers are discovered and merged into a single registry.\n- [ ] AC-2: A workflow name appearing in two or more layers raises `WorkflowNameCollision` with all conflicting paths.\n- [ ] AC-3: A workflow failing API validation raises `InvalidWorkflow` naming layer, path, and violation.\n- [ ] AC-4: Both errors are fatal — no subcommand runs until resolved.\n- [ ] AC-5: Error messages include actionable remediation hints.\n- [ ] AC-6: Unit tests cover all layer combinations, collision pairs, and validation failure modes.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1859,"cache_read_input_tokens":29551,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1859},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"939fc375-8ed1-4dc0-8515-8b3ee2d79451","uuid":"b794c7ad-ece3-4a91-b0e1-96788ec86cf8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013RAKc8zrtpL1u6DDif5cva","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/prds/PRD-222.5-cascade-resolver-workflows.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"939fc375-8ed1-4dc0-8515-8b3ee2d79451","uuid":"e0922240-b30f-4230-9f57-d55448d1127b","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:40:15.051Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/prds/PRD-222.5-cascade-resolver-workflows.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-222.5\"\ntitle: \"Cascade resolver for workflows\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: m\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-222-general-purpose-tool]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.1-config-directory-discovery]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-222.3-bundle-builtin-workflows]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-222.4-user-config-directory]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.8-dogfood-move-state]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/loader.py\n  - src/darkfactory/registry.py\n  - tests/test_registry.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - config\n---\n\n# Cascade resolver for workflows\n\n## Summary\n\nBuild a unified workflow registry that discovers workflows from all three layers (built-in, user, project), validates each against the workflow API contract, and enforces strict name uniqueness across layers. Any name collision is a hard error at startup. Any workflow failing API validation is a hard error with a clear diagnostic message naming the layer, file path, and specific violation.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/registry.py` with a `build_workflow_registry(project_dir: Path | None) -> dict[str, Workflow]` function.\n2. The registry collects workflows from three layers in order:\n   - **Built-in**: from `darkfactory.workflows.get_builtin_workflows()` (PRD-222.3).\n   - **User**: from `~/.config/darkfactory/workflows/` via `load_workflows()` (PRD-222.4 paths).\n   - **Project**: from `<project>/.darkfactory/workflows/` via `load_workflows()` (PRD-222.1 discovery).\n3. **Collision detection**: if any workflow name appears in more than one layer, raise `WorkflowNameCollision` with a message naming all conflicting paths. This is fatal — no subcommand runs.\n4. **API validation**: every discovered workflow is validated at load time against the expected contract (must be a `Workflow` instance with required attributes: `name`, `steps`, `applies_to`). Failures raise `InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, reason)`. Fatal.\n5. Both error types print actionable remediation hints:\n   - Collision: \"Workflow 'X' found in multiple layers: [paths]. Rename or delete one to resolve.\"\n   - Invalid: \"Workflow at [path] (layer: [layer]) failed validation: [reason].\"\n6. Replace the current `_load_workflows_or_fail` in `cli.py` with a call to `build_workflow_registry()`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/registry.py`\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom darkfactory.models import Workflow\nfrom darkfactory.loader import load_workflows\nfrom darkfactory.workflows import get_builtin_workflows\nfrom darkfactory.paths import user_workflows_dir\n\nclass WorkflowNameCollision(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised when the same workflow name appears in multiple layers.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\nclass InvalidWorkflow(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a workflow fails API contract validation.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\ndef _validate_workflow(wf: Workflow, layer: str, path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Validate a workflow against the expected API contract.\"\"\"\n    if not hasattr(wf, 'name') or not wf.name:\n        raise InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, \"'name' attribute is missing or empty\")\n    if not hasattr(wf, 'steps') or not isinstance(wf.steps, list):\n        raise InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, f\"'steps' must be a list; got {type(wf.steps).__name__}\")\n    if not hasattr(wf, 'applies_to') or not callable(wf.applies_to):\n        raise InvalidWorkflow(layer, path, \"'applies_to' must be callable\")\n\ndef build_workflow_registry(project_dir: Path | None = None) -> dict[str, Workflow]:\n    \"\"\"Discover, validate, and return all workflows from all layers.\"\"\"\n    registry: dict[str, tuple[str, Path, Workflow]] = {}\n\n    # Layer 1: built-in\n    for name, wf in get_builtin_workflows().items():\n        _validate_workflow(wf, \"built-in\", Path(\"<package>\") / name)\n        registry[name] = (\"built-in\", Path(\"<package>\") / name, wf)\n\n    # Layer 2: user\n    user_dir = user_workflows_dir()\n    if user_dir.is_dir():\n        for name, wf in load_workflows(user_dir).items():\n            _validate_workflow(wf, \"user\", user_dir / name)\n            if name in registry:\n                existing_layer, existing_path, _ = registry[name]\n                raise WorkflowNameCollision(name, [\n                    (existing_layer, existing_path),\n                    (\"user\", user_dir / name),\n                ])\n            registry[name] = (\"user\", user_dir / name, wf)\n\n    # Layer 3: project\n    if project_dir:\n        proj_wf_dir = project_dir / \"workflows\"\n        if proj_wf_dir.is_dir():\n            for name, wf in load_workflows(proj_wf_dir).items():\n                _validate_workflow(wf, \"project\", proj_wf_dir / name)\n                if name in registry:\n                    existing_layer, existing_path, _ = registry[name]\n                    raise WorkflowNameCollision(name, [\n                        (existing_layer, existing_path),\n                        (\"project\", proj_wf_dir / name),\n                    ])\n                registry[name] = (\"project\", proj_wf_dir / name, wf)\n\n    return {name: wf for name, (_, _, wf) in registry.items()}\n```\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\n- Replace `_load_workflows_or_fail()` (line 90) with a call to `build_workflow_registry(darkfactory_dir)`.\n- Error handling: catch `WorkflowNameCollision` and `InvalidWorkflow` in `main()`, print the message, and exit 1.\n\n### `tests/test_registry.py`\n\nTable-driven tests covering:\n- Built-in only (no user/project dirs).\n- User-only workflows discovered correctly.\n- Project-only workflows discovered correctly.\n- Built-in + project with no collision — all merged.\n- Collision between built-in and user.\n- Collision between built-in and project.\n- Collision between user and project.\n- Invalid workflow in each layer (missing name, bad steps type, non-callable applies_to).\n- Each error message includes layer, path, and specific violation.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: Workflows from all three layers are discovered and merged into a single registry.\n- [ ] AC-2: A workflow name appearing in two or more layers raises `WorkflowNameCollision` with all conflicting paths.\n- [ ] AC-3: A workflow failing API validation raises `InvalidWorkflow` naming layer, path, and violation.\n- [ ] AC-4: Both errors are fatal — no subcommand runs until resolved.\n- [ ] AC-5: Error messages include actionable remediation hints.\n- [ ] AC-6: Unit tests cover all layer combinations, collision pairs, and validation failure modes.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VBLsryvRxb2UxZXaBhoZn6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015hQU7hou3vgmL9Xrph9BDD","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/prds/PRD-222.6-cascade-resolver-config.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-222.6\"\ntitle: \"Cascade resolver for config\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: m\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-222-general-purpose-tool]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.1-config-directory-discovery]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-222.4-user-config-directory]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.8-dogfood-move-state]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/config.py\n  - src/darkfactory/style.py\n  - tests/test_config.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - config\n---\n\n# Cascade resolver for config\n\n## Summary\n\nGeneralize the style-only config resolution from `style.py` into a shared `darkfactory.config` module that merges settings across all layers: built-in defaults < user-level `config.toml` < project-level `config.toml` < env vars < CLI flags. The existing style config resolver (`resolve_style_config` in `style.py`) is refactored to consume the resolved `Config` object instead of resolving its own cascade. This establishes the single config resolution path used by all features.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/config.py` with a `resolve_config()` function that performs the full cascade merge.\n2. Config cascade order (later wins, key-by-key merge):\n   - Built-in defaults (hardcoded in the module)\n   - User-level: `~/.config/darkfactory/config.toml`\n   - Project-level: `<project>/.darkfactory/config.toml`\n   - Environment variables (prefixed with `DARKFACTORY_`)\n   - CLI flags\n3. Define the config schema as a dataclass or typed dict covering:\n   - `[model]` — model defaults per capability tier (trivial, simple, moderate, complex)\n   - `[timeouts]` — effort-based timeout overrides (from PRD-542)\n   - `[style]` — theme, icon_set, no_color (from PRD-541)\n   - Extensible for future sections without breaking existing configs\n4. TOML parsing uses Python stdlib `tomllib` (3.11+).\n5. Refactor `style.py`'s `resolve_style_config()` to read from the resolved `Config` object rather than doing its own file loading. Remove the duplicate `_merge_toml_file` logic from `style.py`.\n6. Env var mapping convention: `DARKFACTORY_MODEL_TRIVIAL` maps to `config.model.trivial`, `DARKFACTORY_STYLE_THEME` maps to `config.style.theme`, etc.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/config.py`\n\n```python\nimport tomllib\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom darkfactory.paths import user_config_file\n\n@dataclass\nclass ModelConfig:\n    trivial: str = \"haiku\"\n    simple: str = \"sonnet\"\n    moderate: str = \"sonnet\"\n    complex: str = \"opus\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass StyleConfig:\n    theme: str = \"dark\"\n    icon_set: str = \"ascii\"\n    no_color: bool = False\n\n@dataclass\nclass Config:\n    model: ModelConfig = field(default_factory=ModelConfig)\n    style: StyleConfig = field(default_factory=StyleConfig)\n    # Extensible: add timeouts, etc.\n\ndef _load_toml(path: Path) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Load a TOML file, returning {} if absent.\"\"\"\n    if not path.is_file():\n        return {}\n    with open(path, \"rb\") as f:\n        return tomllib.load(f)\n\ndef _merge_section(target, section_data: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Merge a dict into a dataclass, key-by-key.\"\"\"\n    for key, value in section_data.items():\n        if hasattr(target, key):\n            setattr(target, key, value)\n\ndef resolve_config(\n    project_dir: Path | None = None,\n    env: dict[str, str] | None = None,\n    cli_overrides: dict | None = None,\n) -> Config:\n    \"\"\"Resolve config through the full cascade.\"\"\"\n    config = Config()\n\n    # Layer 1: user config\n    user_file = user_config_file()\n    if user_file:\n        user_data = _load_toml(user_file)\n        _merge_section(config.model, user_data.get(\"model\", {}))\n        _merge_section(config.style, user_data.get(\"style\", {}))\n\n    # Layer 2: project config\n    if project_dir:\n        proj_file = project_dir / \"config.toml\"\n        proj_data = _load_toml(proj_file)\n        _merge_section(config.model, proj_data.get(\"model\", {}))\n        _merge_section(config.style, proj_data.get(\"style\", {}))\n\n    # Layer 3: env vars\n    # Layer 4: CLI flags\n    # (applied by caller or via helper)\n\n    return config\n```\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/style.py`\n\n- Remove `_merge_toml_file` and the file-loading logic from `resolve_style_config()` (around line 380).\n- `resolve_style_config()` accepts a `Config` object and reads `config.style.*` instead of loading TOML files itself.\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\n- Call `resolve_config(darkfactory_dir, cli_overrides=...)` early in `main()`.\n- Pass the resolved config to `resolve_style_config()` and other consumers.\n\n### `tests/test_config.py`\n\n- Test built-in defaults when no files exist.\n- Test user config overrides built-in defaults.\n- Test project config overrides user config.\n- Test env vars override project config.\n- Test CLI flags override everything.\n- Test key-by-key merge (partial override doesn't wipe other keys).\n- Test absent config files are handled gracefully.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `resolve_config()` merges layers in the correct order.\n- [ ] AC-2: A key set in project config overrides the same key in user config.\n- [ ] AC-3: Env vars (e.g. `DARKFACTORY_MODEL_TRIVIAL`) override config file values.\n- [ ] AC-4: CLI flags override everything.\n- [ ] AC-5: Partial overrides merge key-by-key without wiping other keys in the same section.\n- [ ] AC-6: `style.py` consumes the resolved `Config` object instead of loading files itself.\n- [ ] AC-7: Absent config files produce no errors (empty merge).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8140,"cache_read_input_tokens":31410,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8140},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"939fc375-8ed1-4dc0-8515-8b3ee2d79451","uuid":"af8564a4-b56c-4bd3-a6fc-582bcd4eefa2"}
