data.items():\n        if hasattr(target, key):\n            setattr(target, key, value)\n\ndef resolve_config(\n    project_dir: Path | None = None,\n    env: dict[str, str] | None = None,\n    cli_overrides: dict | None = None,\n) -> Config:\n    \"\"\"Resolve config through the full cascade.\"\"\"\n    config = Config()\n\n    # Layer 1: user config\n    user_file = user_config_file()\n    if user_file:\n        user_data = _load_toml(user_file)\n        _merge_section(config.model, user_data.get(\"model\", {}))\n        _merge_section(config.style, user_data.get(\"style\", {}))\n\n    # Layer 2: project config\n    if project_dir:\n        proj_file = project_dir / \"config.toml\"\n        proj_data = _load_toml(proj_file)\n        _merge_section(config.model, proj_data.get(\"model\", {}))\n        _merge_section(config.style, proj_data.get(\"style\", {}))\n\n    # Layer 3: env vars\n    # Layer 4: CLI flags\n    # (applied by caller or via helper)\n\n    return config\n```\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/style.py`\n\n- Remove `_merge_toml_file` and the file-loading logic from `resolve_style_config()` (around line 380).\n- `resolve_style_config()` accepts a `Config` object and reads `config.style.*` instead of loading TOML files itself.\n\n### Changes to `src/darkfactory/cli.py`\n\n- Call `resolve_config(darkfactory_dir, cli_overrides=...)` early in `main()`.\n- Pass the resolved config to `resolve_style_config()` and other consumers.\n\n### `tests/test_config.py`\n\n- Test built-in defaults when no files exist.\n- Test user config overrides built-in defaults.\n- Test project config overrides user config.\n- Test env vars override project config.\n- Test CLI flags override everything.\n- Test key-by-key merge (partial override doesn't wipe other keys).\n- Test absent config files are handled gracefully.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `resolve_config()` merges layers in the correct order.\n- [ ] AC-2: A key set in project config overrides the same key in user config.\n- [ ] AC-3: Env vars (e.g. `DARKFACTORY_MODEL_TRIVIAL`) override config file values.\n- [ ] AC-4: CLI flags override everything.\n- [ ] AC-5: Partial overrides merge key-by-key without wiping other keys in the same section.\n- [ ] AC-6: `style.py` consumes the resolved `Config` object instead of loading files itself.\n- [ ] AC-7: Absent config files produce no errors (empty merge).\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VBLsryvRxb2UxZXaBhoZn6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01929UwTG4hM5ePswiagiLCe","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-222-general-purpose-tool/prds/PRD-222.7-package-metadata-installability.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-222.7\"\ntitle: \"Package metadata and installability\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-222-general-purpose-tool]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-222.3-bundle-builtin-workflows]]\"\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - pyproject.toml\n  - README.md\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - packaging\n  - cli\n---\n\n# Package metadata and installability\n\n## Summary\n\nVerify and complete the package metadata so that `uv tool install darkfactory` (or `pipx install`, `pip install`) produces working `prd` and `darkfactory` binaries on the user's PATH. Add `darkfactory` as a secondary entry-point alias. Update the README quickstart to reflect the new installation and project setup flow using `.darkfactory/`.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Verify the existing `[project.scripts]` entry `prd = \"darkfactory.cli:main\"` works via `uv tool install .` from a local checkout.\n2. Add `darkfactory = \"darkfactory.cli:main\"` as a secondary entry point in `[project.scripts]`.\n3. Ensure `src/darkfactory/workflows/` and its subdirectories are included in the built wheel (verify `[tool.setuptools.packages]` or equivalent includes them).\n4. Update README.md quickstart section to show:\n   - `uv tool install darkfactory` (or `pipx install darkfactory`)\n   - `cd ~/my-project && prd init`\n   - `prd status`\n5. README must explicitly document that `.darkfactory/` is the target-project convention.\n6. README must note that darkfactory's own repo uses the same `.darkfactory/` convention — no special cases.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `pyproject.toml` changes\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\nprd = \"darkfactory.cli:main\"\ndarkfactory = \"darkfactory.cli:main\"\n```\n\nVerify that `[tool.setuptools.package-data]` or `[tool.setuptools.packages.find]` includes `darkfactory.workflows` and its subpackages. Since workflows are Python modules (not data files), they should be discovered automatically by `find_packages`, but confirm.\n\n### Verification steps\n\n1. `uv tool install .` from repo root — both `prd` and `darkfactory` commands should be on PATH.\n2. `prd --help` and `darkfactory --help` both work.\n3. `prd list-workflows` shows built-in workflows (post-222.3).\n\n### README.md update\n\nRewrite the quickstart section. Keep the rest of the README intact. The new quickstart:\n\n```markdown\n## Quickstart\n\n### Install\n\n```bash\nuv tool install darkfactory\n# or: pipx install darkfactory\n```\n\n### Set up a project\n\n```bash\ncd ~/my-project\nprd init        # creates .darkfactory/ directory\nprd status      # view PRD status\n```\n\n### Project layout\n\ndarkfactory stores all project state under `.darkfactory/` at your repo root:\n- `.darkfactory/prds/` — PRD files (tracked in git)\n- `.darkfactory/workflows/` — custom workflows (tracked; optional)\n- `.darkfactory/config.toml` — project config (tracked; optional)\n- `.darkfactory/worktrees/` — runtime state (git-ignored)\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `uv tool install .` produces a working `prd` binary on PATH.\n- [ ] AC-2: `uv tool install .` also produces a `darkfactory` alias binary on PATH.\n- [ ] AC-3: Built-in workflows are included in the installed package.\n- [ ] AC-4: README quickstart shows the `prd init` flow with `.darkfactory/`.\n- [ ] AC-5: README documents `.darkfactory/` as the universal project convention.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8140,"cache_read_input_tokens"